<p>New to learning JSP, and trying out passing data between two pages.</p>  <p>I'm wondering if it is possible to pass a javascript variable to <code>session.setAttribute()</code> </p>  <p>At the moment, I can pass a string of text through 2 jsp files like so:</p>  <p>JSP1:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;% String text = "hello"; session.setAttribute("test", text);%&gt; </code></pre>  <p>JSP2:</p>  <pre><code>var someText = "&lt;%=session.getAttribute("test")%&gt;" </code></pre>  <p>which works fine.</p>  <p>However, is it possible to pass through a <code>var</code> into <code>session.setAttribute</code> instead? I store some data in a javascript variable and would like to send it across to the second JSP file.</p>  <p>So for example:</p>  <pre><code>var number = 7; &lt;%session.setAttribute("test", number);%&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I've tried this out and I get the error "number cannot be resolved to a variable"</p>  <p>Thanks!</p>